.TH NEXUS-USER 1 "November 2025" "Nexus CLI 0.11.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nexus-user \- user management commands for Nexus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nexus user
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
User management commands for Nexus graph database.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List all users in the system.
.TP
.B create \fIUSERNAME\fR
Create a new user with the specified username.
.TP
.B get \fIUSERNAME\fR
Get information about a specific user.
.TP
.B delete \fIUSERNAME\fR
Delete a user from the system.
.SH OPTIONS FOR CREATE
.TP
.BR \-\-password " " \fIPASS\fR
Set the user's password (required).
.TP
.BR \-\-roles " " \fIROLES\fR
Comma-separated list of roles to assign.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List all users:
.B nexus user list
.TP
Create a new user:
.B nexus user create myuser --password secret --roles admin,reader
.TP
Get user info:
.B nexus user get myuser
.TP
Delete a user:
.B nexus user delete myuser
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nexus (1),
.BR nexus-key (1)
